i8B71S9Ewy3weVbPgyn4L2HFkTgiD_eN1q-8GL_lWDFigF8_8md0CW5K_Mb7Z-BsujWGx4N4fwMHSCUDeG-v_G6WwIhR8eAm7naQXhBgQo4PGSra_EFR6vyxwtBgc9UDTPdYKQX51EXooIsz7qMEWsibRHzeVNgMsjcXX2kwiJ85cXUXbEEbIkfZ__7FPkebtp3ZAgM6tMHVbCh9ud6VEk8Txz4j2hLkCQe8hZywWsxOhgKLMY60B2JcDXT75cvCeYNXj1ZIJkY5PCr9_0yU8M-73NiSLC56D0-f3TL6pkWPqbOCbWJCeUW2Epxa4qSarcYAIrharg277HmHZqP6NacvVBlMnM7fneR-ggv9S2ZesuAjaC4h7kLqBbBYd6R6aed5euIFs5bH_V3f9gDXY1W9\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about finding the Class resource in the Javassist jar using Loader.class's classloader. I wonder if native resources from dependencies include metadata; if it works, I might face challenges with duplicate Javassist classes. I just need to call getResourceAsStream, and if the native resource isn't included, it returns null. Then, I can load the class and delegate to the parent to load the existing class. Testing should confirm whether the returned class works as expected.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AuCB3DK0DxpkwuKtB2VKrAlq|fc_0bbcb0a069182a090169f9ccc9153481959efa1091fa5f87f7", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/LoaderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javassist.javassist;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n\nimport javassist.Loader;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class LoaderTest {\n    @AfterEach\n    void resetFixtureState() {\n        MainFixture.receivedArguments = new String[0];\n        MainFixture.invocationCount = 0;\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void runLoadsDelegatedClassAndInvokesItsMainMethod() throws Throwable {\n        Loader loader = new Loader(getClass().getClassLoader(), null);\n        loader.delegateLoadingOf(MainFixture.class.getName());\n\n        loader.run(MainFixture.class.getName(), new String[] {\"alpha\", \"beta\"});\n\n        assertThat(MainFixture.invocationCount).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(MainFixture.receivedArguments).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void delegatesBootstrapClassLookupToSystemClassLoaderWhenParentIsNull() throws Exception {\n        Loader loader = new Loader(null, null);\n\n        Class<?> loadedClass = loader.loadClass(String.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(String.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsClassBytesAsResourceBeforeDefiningNonDelegatedClass() throws Exception {\n        Loader loader = new Loader(getClass().getClassLoader(), null);\n\n        try {\n            Class<?> loadedClass = loader.loadClass(\"javassist.CtClass\");\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass.getName()).isEqualTo(\"javassist.CtClass\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class MainFixture {\n        private static String[] receivedArguments = new String[0];\n        private static int invocationCount;\n\n        public static void main(String[] args) {\n            receivedArguments = Arrays.copyOf(args, args.length);\n            invocationCount++;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 782, "output": 2338, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32304, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777978541375, "responseId": "resp_0bbcb0a069182a090169f9ccaf741081958939061b5c744318"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_AuCB3DK0DxpkwuKtB2VKrAlq